{"title_page": "Borders of India", "text_new": "{{cleanup|reason=Strangely formatted text in sections below.|date=January 2018}}\n[[File:Open Border - India, Nepal, Bhutan.png|India shares an [[open border|open land border]] with [[Nepal]] and [[Bhutan]].|thumb|right]]\n\nIndia shares with many sovereign countries; Nepal, Pakistan, China, Bangladesh, Burma, Bhutan, Sri Lanka and Afghanistan.\n\n==Land borders of India==\n{{anchor| Land }}\n \n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Land Border Country\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" |Length (m) and (m)<ref name=\"ejyoti.com\">[http://www.ejyoti.com/facts-about-india/548-list-of-countries-where-india-shares-its-political-borders.htm eJyoti Discovering facts, Information website ]</ref>\n! Force\n! Comments\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Bangladesh}} [[Bangladesh\u2013India border|Bangladesh]] || {{convert|4096|km|mi|abbr=}}||[[Border Security Force]] || [[India\u2013Bangladesh enclaves]] exchanged. \n|-\n||{{Flagicon|Bhutan}} [[Bhutan\u2013India border|Bhutan]]||{{convert|699|km|mi|abbr=}}<ref name=\"toi1\">[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/ssb-to-strengthen-presence-on-india-bhutan-border/articleshow/62181663.cms SSB to strengthen presence on India-Bhutan border], Times of India, 20 Dec 2017.</ref>||[[Sashastra Seema Bal]]|| Open border\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|China}} [[McMahon Line|China]] || {{convert|3488|km|mi|abbr=}}||[[Indo-Tibetan Border Police]] and [[Special Frontier Force]] || Also see [[McMahon Line]].  \n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Myanmar}} [[India\u2013Myanmar barrier|Myanmar]] || {{convert|1643|km|mi}}  || [[Assam Rifles]] and [[Indian Army]] || \n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Nepal}} [[Nepal]] || {{convert|1751|km|mi|abbr=}}<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/ssb-to-strengthen-presence-on-india-bhutan-border/articleshow/62181663.cms</ref>||[[Sashastra Seema Bal]]  || Open border.\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Pakistan}} [[India\u2013Pakistan border|Pakistan]] || {{convert|3323|km|mi}}  || [[Border Security Force]] || Also see [[Radcliffe Line]], [[Operation Meghdoot]] and [[Sir Creek]]. \n|- \n|}\n\n== Maritime borders of India ==\n{{anchor| Maritime }}\n\n'''Maritime borders of India''' are the [[maritime boundary]] recognized by the [[United Nations Convention on the Law of the Sea]] entails boundaries of [[territorial waters]], [[contiguous zone]]s, and [[exclusive economic zones]]. India, with its claim of a {{convert|12|NM|sing=on}} territorial maritime zone and {{convert|200|NM|sing=on}} exclusive economic zone, has a more than {{convert|7000|km|sing=on}} maritime border shared with seven nations.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Maritime Border Country\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" |Length (km) and (mi)<ref name=\"ejyoti.com\"/>\n! Force\n! Comments\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Bangladesh}} [[Bangladesh\u2013India border#Maritime boundary|Bangladesh]] || || [[Indian Navy]] || [[New Moore Island]]\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Indonesia}} [[Indonesia]] || || [[Indian Navy]] || [[Indira Point]]\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Myanmar}} [[Myanmar]] || || [[Indian Navy]] || [[Coco Islands]]\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Pakistan}} [[Pakistan]] || || [[Indian Navy]] || [[Sir Creek]]\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Thailand}} [[India\u2013Thailand relations#India-Thailand maritime boundary|Thailand]] || || [[Indian Navy]] || [[Similan Islands]]\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Sri Lanka}} [[Sri Lanka]] || >{{convert|400|km|mi}}<ref name=SL1>[https://www.iasgs.com/2017/03/fishing-rights-disputes-india-sri-lanka/ India-Sri Lanka fishing rights dispute]</ref> || [[Indian Navy]] || [[Katchatheevu]]\n|-\n|| {{Flagicon|Maldives}} [[Maldives]] || || [[Indian Navy]] || [[Maliku Kandu]]\n|}\n\n==Designated crossings with ICP & LCS ==\n{{anchor | Designated crossings | ICP | LCS }}\n<!-- Convert these to sortable table with several columns. Source cited is old (Oct 2011) and some LCS have been converted to ICP (insert those with new source/citation) and insert any new LCS with source/citation -->\n\nThe [http://www.mdoner.gov.in/zoomimzgemap/zoom-imagemap.php?map=Look%20East%20Policy map of ICP and LCS].\n\n===Integrated Check Posts (ICP) ===\n{{anchor | ICP }}\n\nIndia has 7 functional ICPs, and plans are underway to upgrade 13 more LCS to ICP, including 7 at borders taking total of border ICP to 14, at the cost of {{INRconvert|3000|c}} (c. Oct 2017).<ref name=icp6/><ref name=icp7/> Designated Integrated Check Posts (ICP), with both customs and immigration facilities are:<ref name=icp1>[http://www.mdoner.gov.in/node/1483 ICP of India]</ref>\n\n====[[Bangladesh\u2013India border|India\u2013Bangladesh border]]====\n{{anchor | Bangladesh }}\n\n* [[Assam]]\n** [[Karimganj district#Sutarkandi international border crossing|Karimganj]]-[[Sylhet District|Golapganj uppozilla]] in Sylhet District of  Bangladesh via [[Karimganj district#Sutarkandi international border crossing|Sutarkandi]] integrated checkpost crossing on [[National Highway 37 (India)|NH37]](India) and Sheola post (Sylhet division, Bangladesh), plan announced c. Oct 2017.<ref name=icp6/>\n* [[Meghalaya]]\n** [[Shillong]]-[[Sylhet]] via [[Dawki#Border-crossing|Dawki ICP]] integrated checkpost crossing (Jaintia Hills, India) and Tambil post (Bangladesh). Dawki ICP foundation stone laid in January 2017 and will become operation in 2018.<ref name=icp5>[https://www.telegraphindia.com/1170125/jsp/northeast/story_132223.jsp Dawki ICP foundation stone laid].</ref>\n* [[Mizoram]]\n** Kawrpuichhuah / Kawarpuchiah / Kawripuichhuah near [[Tlabung]] in [[Lunglei district]], opened in Oct 2017.<ref name=icp6/><ref>[https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/india-opens-two-border-crossing-points-with-myanmar-bangladesh/article9883216.ece India opens two border crossing points with Myanmar, Bangladesh], Business Line.</ref><ref name=clar1/>\n* [[Tripura]]\n** [[Agartala]]-[[Dhaka]] via Agartala integrated checkpost (India) and [[Akhaura Upazila|Akhaura]] checkpost crossing, already functional (c. 2017).<ref name=icp7/>\n** \"[[Belonia, India]] - [[Parshuram Upazila|Parshuram, Bangladesh]] road and rail crossing checkposts\" in [[South Tripura district]] which connect the railway from [[Santirbazar]] in India to [[Feni District|Feni]] in Bangladesh. \n* [[West Bengal]] (clockwise from Kolkatta to north)\n**[[Kolkata]]\u2013[[Dhaka]] via [[Petrapole]] integrated checkpost crossing, already functional (c. 2017).<ref name=icp7>[http://www.dhakatribune.com/world/south-asia/2017/10/18/india-plans-to-construct-7-integrated-check-posts-on-bangladesh-border/ 7 border ICP and total 13 ICP coming up]</ref>\n** [[Barasat|Barasat (India) to Ghojadanga (Bangladesh)]], plan announced c. Oct 2017.<ref name=icp6/><ref name=clar2/>\n** [[Mahadipur]] in [[Malda district]] in [[Malda district|Malda]]-[[Rajshahi]] via [[Malda district#Mahadipur international border crossing|Mahadipur]] crossing, in-principal approval in 2019.<ref name=clar2/><ref name=icp6/>\n** [[Fulbari]], plan announced c. Oct 2017.<ref name=icp6/>\n** [[Hili, Dakshin Dinajpur|Hili]], plan announced c. Oct 2017.<ref name=\"icp6\">[http://indianexpress.com/article/india/centre-plans-13-new-integrated-check-posts-to-encourage-engagement-with-neighbours-4895820/], Indian Express, Oct 2017.</ref>\n** [[Changrabandha railway station]], in-principal approval in 2019.<ref name=clar2>[https://nenow.in/north-east-news/delhi-approves-sutarkandi-integrated-check-post-along-indo-bangla-border.html Delhi approves Sutarkandi integrated check post along Indo-Bangla border], North East News, 7 Jan 2019.</ref>\n\n====[[Bhutan\u2013India border|India-Bhutan border]]====\n{{anchor | Bhutan }}\n\n* [[Jaigaon]] at [[Alipurduar district]] of West Bengal, plan approved c. 2016.<ref name=nep1/>\n\n====[[India\u2013Myanmar barrier|India\u2013Myanmar border]]====\n{{anchor | Myanmar | Burma }}\n\n* [[Moreh, India#Integrated Check Post (ICP) Moreh|Moreh ICP]], already operational.<ref name=icp4/>\n* [[Zochachhuah|Zochawchhuah]] ([[Lawngtlai district]] in India) - Zorinpui (Myanmar) at Indo-Myanmar border on [[Kaladan Multi-Modal Transit Transport Project]] has already been operational since Oct 2017.<ref name=icp4>[https://www.google.com.sg/search?client=firefox-b&dcr=0&ei=lWJCWr3sLcrJvgS0ory4CA&q=zorinpui+lawngtlai+&oq=zorinpui+lawngtlai+&gs_l=psy-ab.3...5050.12763.0.13049.20.20.0.0.0.0.285.2665.0j13j2.15.0....0...1c.1.64.psy-ab..5.10.1914...0j0i67k1j0i131k1j0i10k1j0i13k1.0.d3bPEkKCEM4 India opens two border crossing points with Myanmar, Bangladesh], [[Times of India]], 1 Oct 2o17.</ref><ref name=clar1>[https://tradeandcommerce.mizoram.gov.in/page/12th-five-year-plan.html 12th Five Year Plan]</ref> The 22 km long Lunglei\u2013Tlabung\u2013Kawrpuichhuah road was upgraded in 2014-15 in a [[World Bank]]-funded project to enhance India-Bangladesh border connectivity.<ref>[http://www.worldbank.org/en/news/press-release/2014/06/12/107-million-world-bank-project-to-connect-mizoram-with-bangladesh-and-myanmar-via-roads $107 Million World Bank Project to Connect Mizoram with Bangladesh and Myanmar via Roads], [[World Bank]].</ref> Survey for the Rail line from [[Sairang]] to [[Hmawngbuchhuah]] (1 km north of Zochawchhuah) was completed in August 2017 and it will be constructed in future phase.<ref name=railline1>[http://www.powerupconstruction.com/indias-north-east-opensthe-gateway-to-prosperity/ India's north east opened up], PowerUpConstruction.Com</ref>\n\n====[[India\u2013Nepal relations#Border crossings|India-Nepal border]]====\n{{anchor | Nepal }}\n\n* [[Banbasa]] in [[Champawat district]] of Uttrakhand, in-principle approval in 2019.<ref name=clar2/>\n* [[Bhitamore]]/Bhittamore in [[Sitamarhi district]] of Bihar, in-principle approval in 2019.<ref name=clar2/>\n* [[Jogbani]], Bihar<ref name=nep1>[https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/indo-nepal-and-indo-bhutan-border-to-have-more-integrated-check-posts/articleshow/52964568.cms Indo-Nepal and Indo-Bhutan border to have more ICP], Oct 2016.</ref> \t\n* [[Panitanki]], [[Darjeeling district]] of West Bengal,<ref name=nep1/> in-principal approval in 2019.<ref name=clar2/>\n* [[Raxaul]], Bihar<ref name=nep1/>\n* [[Sonauli#Sonauli India-Nepal border crossing|Sonauli]], Uttar Pradesh{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}\n* [[Rupaidiha]], Uttar Pradesh<ref name=nep1/>\n* [[Taulihawa]]-[[Siddharthnagar]], Uttar Pradesh<ref name=nep1/>\n\n====[[India\u2013Pakistan border#Border crossings|India\u2013Pakistan border]]====\n{{anchor | Pakistan }}\n{{see also|Transport between India and Pakistan}}\n\n* [[Attari]] at [[Wagah]] in Punjab, already operational (2017) (see [[Samjhauta Express]]).\n* [[Munabao]] in [[Barmer district]] in [[Rajasthan]] (see [[Thar Express]])\n\n===Land Customs Stations (LCS) ===\n{{anchor | LCS }}\n\n====[[Bangladesh\u2013India border|India\u2013Bangladesh border]]====\nDesignated Land Customs Stations (LCS) are (no immigration facilities):<ref name=icp11>[http://www.mdoner.gov.in/sites/default/files/silo2_content/Look%20East%20Policy/RIS%20Border%20Trade%20Report%20-%20final.pdf ICP and LCS]</ref>\n\n* [[Assam]]\n** [[Mankachar]] Land Customs Stations (India) - Rowmari post (Natun Bandar, Rongpur division, Bangladesh)\n** [[Karimganj]] Steamer and Ferry Station (KSFS) (India) - Zakiganj post (Sylhet division, Bangladesh)\n** [[Dhubri district|Guwahati Steamer Ghat]] ([[Dhubri district]], India) -\n** [[Dhubri|Dhubri Steamer Ghat]] (Dhubri district, India) - Rowmati (Maymansingh division, Bangladesh)\n** Assam non-functional LCS are:\n*** [[Mahisasan railway station]] (Karimganj district, India) - Shahbazpur (Sylhet division)\n*** [[Golokganj]] (Dhubri district) - Sonahaat (Rongpur Division)\n*** [[Silchar railway station|Silchar Railway Mail Service]] (India) - independent of border (no border, inland LCS)\n* [[West Bengal]]\n* [[Meghalaya]]\n** [[Baghmara, India|Baghmara]] (South Garo Hills, India) - Bijoyour post (Bangladesh)\n** [[East Khasi Hills district|Bholaganj]] (East Khasi Hills district) - Chatak (Sunamganj division)\n** Borsara Land Customs Stations (West Khasi Hills, India) - Borsara post (Bangladesh)\n** [[West Garo Hills district#Economy|West Garo Hills]] - [[Baksiganj Upazila|Bakshiganj]] via [[West Garo Hills district#Mahendraganj international border crossing|Mahendraganj]] crossing on [[National Highway 217 (India)|NH12]] \n** [[Tura, Meghalaya|Tura]]-[[Nalitabari Upazila|Nalitabari]] via [[Dalu, Meghalaya|Dalu]] crossing on [[National Highway 217 (India)|NH217]] (West Garo Hills, India) and Nakugaon post (Bangladesh)\n** [[West Khasi Hills district|Shellabazar]] (West Khasi Hills district) - Sunamganj(Sylhet division)\n** [[South Garo Hills district|Gasuapara]] (South Garo Hills district)- Karoitol (Mymansing division)\n** Meghalaya non-functional LCS are:\n*** [[Mawsynram|Ryngku]] (East Khasi Hills district) - Kalibari (Sonamganj division)\n*** [[Balat, Meghalaya|Balat]] (East Khasi Hills district) - Dolura (Sylhet division)\n* [[Tripura]]\n** [[Sipahijala district|Srimantapur]] ([[Sipahijala district]]) - Bibir Bazar (Comilla division), became operational in January 2016.<ref name=lcs2>[https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2016/01/07/tripura-opens-new-land-customs-station-along-bangladesh-border Srimantapur LCS opens]</ref> \n** [[Dhalai district|Dhalaighat]] ([[Dhalai district]]) - Kumarghat (Sunamganj division) \n** [[Khowai]]ghat ([[West Tripura district]]) - Balla (Habiganj division)  \n** [[Manu, Tripura|Manu]] (Dhalai district) - Chatlapur (Sylhet division )\n** [[South Tripura district|Muhurighat]] ([[South Tripura district]]) -  Belonia (Feni division )\n** [[North Tripura district|Old Ragnabazar]] ([[North Tripura district]]) - Betul (Fultali) (Sylhet division)\n* [[Mizoram]]\n** Kawarpuchiah integrated checkpost, opened in Oct 2017 by Prime Minister Narendra Modi.<ref name=pm1>[http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/india-opens-two-border-crossing-points-with-myanmar-bangladesh/article9883216.ece India opens two border crossing points with Myanmar, Bangladesh]</ref>\n** Non-functional LCS in Mizoram:\n*** [[Tlabung|Demagiri]] (Lunglei district) - Rangamati (Sylhet division)\n\n====[[India\u2013Pakistan border#Border crossings|India\u2013Pakistan border]]====\n{{div col|colwidth=15em}}\n* [[Longewala]] in [[Jaisalmer district]] of Rajsthan\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Border bazaars and haats==\n{{anchor | markets | market | haats | haat | bazaar | bazaars }}\n<!-- NOTE: Old data/source from June 2011. This section needs updating. Also convert it to a sortable table format with multiple columns to capture location and functional status -->\nThis proposed list of border [[bazaar]]s and [[Haat bazaar|haat]]s is in varying stages of implementation, as suggested by State Governments to the [[Ministry of External Affairs (India)|Ministry of External Affairs]] for setting up Border Haats.<ref name=haat1>[http://www.mdoner.gov.in/node/1485 Border haats of India]</ref>\n\n===[[India\u2013Myanmar barrier|India\u2013Myanmar border]]===\nAs of April 2012, India and Myanmar have approved two locations \u2013 Pangsau Pass, Arunachal Pradesh and Somrai in Ukhrul District.  These are likely to be finalised soon during a forthcoming visit of Hon\u2019ble Prime Minister to Myanmar.<ref name=haat1/>\n\n** [[Arunachal Pradesh]] Border Haats\n** Pangsau Pass (Nampong), Changlang - Pangsau, Kachin Province \t \n** Chingsa (Khimiyang Circle), Changlang - Langhong, Kachin Province\n** Makantong (Khimiyang Circle), Changlang - Ngaimong, Kachin Province\n** Wakka/Pongchao/Lazu - Tirap, Kachin Province\n* [[Manipur]] Border Haats\n*** Kongkan Thana, Ukhrul - Aungci \tSuggested by State Government\n*** New Somtal, Chandel - Thenjen, or Khampat\n*** Behiang, Churachandpur - Khenman, or Chikha\n* [[Mizoram]] Border Haats\n** Hruitezawl, Lawngtlai - Varang\n** Hnahlan, Champhai - Darkhai\n** Vaphai, Champhai - Leilet\n** Chakhang, Saiha - Nviaphia\n* [[Nagaland]] Border Haats\n** Avakhung, Phek - Layshi are 32&nbsp;km from each other \t\n** Pangsha, Tuensang - Lahe/Hkamti District HQ are 60&nbsp;km from each other\n** Chemoho/Longwa, Mon - Lahe \tare 60&nbsp;km from each other\n** Molhe, Phek - Pansat are 10&nbsp;km from each other\n\n=== [[Bangladesh\u2013India border|India\u2013Bangladesh border]]===\n** [[Meghalaya]]\n***  Kalaichar, West Garo Hills \t\n***  Balat, West Khasi Hills\n** [[Mizoram]]\n***  Marpara, Mamit - Longkor \t \n***  Sillsury, Lunglei - Mahmuam \t \n***  Tuipuibari, Mamit - Not provided\n***  Nunsuri, Lunglei - Not provided\n** [[Tripura]]: Decision  on Tripura Haats will be subsequent to the completion of agreement w.r.t. Meghalaya Haats.\n***  Kamalasagar, West Tripura\n***  Boxanagar\n***  Bamutia\n***  Srinagar, South Tripura\n***  Ekimpur\n***  Pal Basti (Raghna), North Tripura\n***  Hiracherra (Kailasahar)\n***  Kamalpur, Dhalai\n\n== In popular media ==\n{{anchor | popular }}\n{{expand section|date=December 2019}}\n\nPradeep Damodaran's book ''\"Borderlands: travels across India's boundaries\" chronicles all land borders of India.<ref name=sl1>[https://scroll.in/article/830499/what-will-you-see-if-you-visit-the-precise-point-where-india-ends-and-sri-lanka-begins What will you see if you visit the precise point where India ends and Sri Lanka begins?], Scroll.in, 1 March 2017.</ref> The [[bollywood]] director [[J. P. Dutta]] has specialised in making [[Hindi language|Hindi]] movies with India's border as key element of the theme, his movies are [[Border (1997 film)]], [[Refugee (2000 film)]], [[LOC: Kargil]], [[Paltan (film)]], etc.<ref name=lineinsand1>Adrian M. Athique, 2010, [https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/00856400802441920?scroll=top&needAccess=true&journalCode=csas20 A Line in the Sand: The India\u2013Pakistan Border in the Films of J.P. Dutta], Centre for Critical and Cultural Studies, University of Queensland, Pages 472-499. \nIt is a very big border!</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{col div|colwidth=22em}}\n; India related\n* [[List of extreme points of India|Extreme points of India]]\n* [[Look East policy (India)